The paper deals with cooperative games and their solution concepts, which are typically studied in the field of game theory (cs.GT). The use of propositional formulas to represent player preferences suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), where logical representations are commonly used. The study of partitioning and equivalence classes is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the succinct representation of games, which is a topic in machine learning and computational complexity (cs.LG). Finally, the study of coalitions and preferences can be seen as a topic in social choice theory (cs.SI).
